parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AYC/ACD pump can cause issues with the vehicle's all-wheel control system, leading to loss of traction, reduced vehicle stability, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience slow acceleration
and may display warning lights or messages related to the all-wheel control system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when accelerating, leading to reduced vehicle performance, increased risk of accidents, and potential transmission failure.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience slow acceleration
and may display warning lights or messages related to the transmission. In some cases
the vehicle may shift out of gear or into neutral while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and engine noise can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when accelerating, leading to reduced vehicle performance, increased risk of accidents, and potential transmission failure.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience gears slipping out while accelerating
causing the RPMs to shoot up
and may produce unusual engine noises

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Differential and CV Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential and CV joint can cause the vehicle to vibrate, drag, or lose power, leading to reduced vehicle performance, increased risk of accidents, and potential transmission failure.
A faulty serpentine belt and tensioner can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on and off
the battery light comes on and off with a noise

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature catalytic converter failure can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, leading to environmental harm and potential health risks.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on with a P0420 code
the vehicle fails to pass emissions tests.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Central computer failure can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to accelerate, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls with no warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Alternator and charging system failure can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the battery is completely dead and will not hold a charge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion failure of the front subframe can cause the control arm to dismount and the CV axle to separate from the transmission, leading to a loss of steering control and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: unusual noises or vibrations while driving
separation of the CV axle from the transmission

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The squeaking noise from the steering wheel can be a sign of a underlying issue with the steering system, which can lead to a loss of steering control and potentially result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Squeaking noise from the steering wheel
unusual vibrations or noises while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can cause reduced visibility during rain or snow, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wiper blades stop moving or get stuck in the middle of the wiping motion
the wiper blades stop moving when the car is stationary or moving
the wiper motor starts working again after being turned off and back on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the windshield wiper linkage can cause the wiper blades to malfunction, reducing visibility during rain or snow, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wiper blades stop moving or get stuck in the middle of the wiping motion
the wiper blades do not move smoothly
